summary: Killing Eve’s Jodie Comer reveals she still lives at home with parents
title: Killing Eve’s Jodie Comer reveals she still lives at home with parents
excerpt: Killing Eve star Jodie Comer has revealed she is trying not to be daunted by her new-found fame in the hit BBC show - and still wants to live at home with her parents. The actress, 25, plays psychopathic assassin Oksana Astankova opposite Sandra Oh’s MI5 officer Eve Polastri in the critically acclaimed BBC America series.
description: “I live in Liverpool, still at home with my mum and dad. I get the best of both worlds. I’m here now for six months [filming in London], but as soon as that six months is over, there’s nowhere else I want to go other than home … I just love Liverpool. I love London, but I like to leave.”

summary: ok im just abt to start this little chain of observations here on tumblr because i have no friends to actually discuss these. so...
body:
ok im just abt to start this little chain of observations here on tumblr because i have no friends to actually discuss these. so im just gonna dive in

im gonna title this villanelle & men bc im shit at titles

Oksana grew up in a dysfunctional family. She had a drunk dad, mum died for a reason that we don’t know yet (and tbh id love to be informed abt her past, her childhood, family, school friends etc) However there is no proof that this is the cause of her torture against men. The murders are more symbolic than ‘enjoying the process’ anyway as if she is trying to give a message, which then means that it is for others and not for herself. Most of the time she will kill them first, but there were some occasions she watches them suffer. I wonder what the difference is. The type of torture could also indicate something and I am hoping for the show to reveal that later (like, why their balls? why not decorate them in an embarrassing way? why not make food out of them? why is it just that area?)

She is sapphic, could be lesbian because she didn’t seem to enjoy sex with men so far (except for the threesome but even that one is blurry). Even though she seems to target men in this way, she doesn’t seem to hate all men. Maybe just their penises lol idk.

Her relationship with Konstantin is interesting, we know she is attracted to older women. What about older men? We know she wants him to care about her, she asks such questions to check. Plays dead, 

asks if he saved her from being removed (from the job, last episodes). I wonder if she ever saw him as a potential romantic partner or was it more like a father-daughter relationship? In the first episode, she asks them if they can watch a movie together, as in the last episode she says she is just looking for someone to watch movies with. 

She never made an attempt but she also asks him why he never tried to have sex with her all this time (in a purely curious way, not heartbroken, not offended). I personally dont think it is romantic at all, but i also doubt what romantic means for Oksana, she had a strange relationship with Anna as well and she has a thing for older people.

Constantine is an excellent liar who can manage several people and identities at the same time. I’d say he has some anti-social traits himself. Remember how he tried to manipulate her feelings, he knows she isnt a psycho.

He seems to care about villanelle, but not sure if he can really understand him because he is always cautious. When she kidnapped the kids, i find it peculiar that he didnt fear for her daughter’s life but instead he said she will annoy her a lot. That means he understands her, and having the pills all set up also means he knew her next move. Why wont he let her come closer though? What is Villanelle’s tendency that Konstantin doesnt like? We know for sure that one person he cares about the most is his daughter. And even when villanelle is in danger somehow we dont see that little twitch on his face. 

Villanelle also seems to have a sister-like relationship with the daughter, arguing with her like little kids and not hurting her anyway.

Also what is the connection between the women Oksana loved and the closest men in their lives? Oksana loves Anna, she kills her husband, throws a party with a huge cake. Oksana loves Eve, kills Bill (who seemed like a husband but she knew he wasnt the one), throws a party with a huge cake. 

She throws a party for these people’s death, almost like a birthday party. dunno, birth of the freed women she loved? I cant tell how Bill effected eve though, considering she was more married to her job we could say the Boss was the husband. Anna complained abt her husband to her, when did Eve complain about Bill that she heard about it


ok now its your turn
